        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 12:44PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 1244 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Albuquerque, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albuquerque, Corrales, Los Ranchos De Albuquerque, North Valley,
South Valley, Paradise Hills and Alameda.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 157 and 168.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 221 and 234.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
